parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause extended stopping distances, loss of braking power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle jerks or pulsates when braking
extended stopping distance
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the brake pedal can cause loss of braking power, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal jerks or pulsates when braking
and delayed or incomplete braking response.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause loss of braking power, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaks
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Interference between the clutch and brake systems can cause loss of braking power, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelts can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor works only sometimes
the seatbelt gets caught in the door
the seatbelt is shredded
the seatbelt falls off the B-pillar due to interior rusting
the seatbelt locks up and won't extend to place in latch
the seatbelt latch becomes stuck in an open position
the seatbelt will not catch during sudden stops
the rear seatbelts fail to restrain occupants
rust accumulates around shoulder belt mounting bolts
the seatbelt buckle release button breaks
and the seatbelt locking mechanism sticks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelt buckles can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle fails to latch
the seatbelt buckle release button breaks
the seatbelt buckle sticks
and the seatbelt locking mechanism sticks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelt retractors can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor works only sometimes
the seatbelt gets caught in the door
and the seatbelt locks up and won't extend to place in latch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, damage to vehicle components, and loss of vehicle functionality, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Smoke or fire from the engine compartment
dashboard
or instrument cluster
burning smells
electrical shorts
blown fuses
malfunctioning lights
and radio issues.

symptoms: Smoke or fire from the engine compartment
burning smells
electrical shorts
blown fuses
malfunctioning lights
and alternator failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to fires, damage to vehicle components, and loss of vehicle functionality, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Ignition switch failure
internal shorting

and malfunctioning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion in the rear defrost wiring can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to fires, damage to vehicle components, and loss of vehicle functionality, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Corrosion in the rear defrost wiring
malfunctioning rear defrost system
